column5: 40 degree days with no wind, 2 different lakes and 3 rivers, brought in results we will not complain about. We did our best.  On the other half, we did somethin different from previous trips. Instead of camping in the cheapest possible spot, we rented a cabin for a couple nights. Well worth it. Ammenities, for very little more than a campsite with hydro.  The fish:                  The memories:                And don`t forget, ever, ever, the KAWARTHA DAIRY!    This has been a photo memory journey. Hope you enjoyed a bit of the good life like we did up there.
Forgot some:
Looks like a real good get together for you two. Thanks for showing.  ps. Feed that muskie one of those burgers.
I have a feeling that Hasselhoff has nothing on you guys when it comes to running down the beach in slow motion.  Congratulations on being born and continuing to exist.  Well done.
Looks like a nice trip.  That muskie sure could use some food... Wonder what's wrong with it, just give it a burger!
Nice to see you are still putting the smack down on the WGSF.      Great report Rich, your reports always put a smile on my face.
MMmmmmmmmm..  That's mouth watering!!   Great read Rich!
Nice lads !!!    Good to see the duo back together again...
Great stuff Rich, nice to see a colourful report from you again.  Keep em comin

Good to see you posting again Rich!  I passed a Kawartha Dairy this past weekend heading north and wondered when the annual report was coming out!  Great to see that tradition still happening.  Oh yeah...nice fish too!
You guys know how to make a burger, very impressive!  Keep your hooks sharp!
Rocky XIII  Awesome Report.
Awesome report Rich....you guys did it up right.  Is it possible that someone's been giving that musky some meth?  Really nice bass btw....what was that soft swimbait you were using?  Looks great
rich nice mixed bag of fish
Nice fish guys!
Great collection of fish!!! Good job you two
Wonderful report and those burgers look awesom!  Feed one of thoes to that muskie and it will gain 10 lbs in no time!  Now you know why I like living in the Kawarthas!
Great report guys!!!
cool pics man!... by the way who makes that burger!... lol gotta have one of those!...
Hi Rich, I still remember that day you two came carp fishing with me on your trip (was that the first camping trip you two did?) That's memory.
Nice report but....no onions?
Great report as always Rich it was nice meeting you at the Fish-A-thon all though I dont remember you making it back for dinner and prizes??? I guess you were still out fishing.
Good stuff Rich!!  Food and fishing..."gotta" love it!!
Its been way to long since i have been up there!! I had a great time that's for sure!! Cant wait for anther trip!! this trip i will have the onionsssssssssss lol
Yessir, I stayed out fishing til 8pm. Felt kinda bad, but just couldn't stop fishing. lol  Thanks everyone for the comments. It was an awesome trip as always. Can't wait to go back up.
